1C pass 1D pass 1H pass 2S pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "6eeda228475348205d86c2245265ebc5864f05061754a72a80e55210e237fffb"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/advanced_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has a perfect hand on which to use Fourth Suit Forcing. If East can stop 
\Ss, then 3NT would be a great contract.

There is one problem - if WEST bids 1\S at her second turn it is NOT considered 
FSF, so she must jump to 2\S.

EAST, win a fine \S stopper, bids 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:Q75.JT76.A8.KQJ3 A96.A542.964.842 K8432.KQ83.73.A5 JT.9.KQJT52.T976"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1C pass 1S pass 1NT pass 2D pass 2H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "e4530204b203acc529ddfa56b36d2ce3a48b48bff94d9b4e1f28c49eae736435"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/advanced_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH's 2\D bid is a perfect example of NMF. 
It provides SOUTH with the opportunity to show either a 4-card \H suit, 
OR 3-card \S support.

In this hand SOUTH actually has both. When that happens, showing the \Hs is 
first priority.}

